To implement a C++ function that utilizes the WordNet database to find the antonym of a given word, you can use the `wn` (WordNet) library, which is available for free in C++. The `wn` library provides access to the WordNet database, which contains a vast collection of synonyms, hyponyms, antonyms, and related words.

Here is a basic example of how you can implement such a function:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>
#include <wn.h>

using namespace std;

// Function to find the antonym of a given word
vector<string> findAntonym(string word) {
    vector<string> antonyms;

    // Initialize an empty vector to store antonyms
    for (const auto &synonym : wn.synonym(word)) {
        antonyms.push_back(synonym);
    }

    // Return the antonyms
    return antonyms;
}

